@startuml correction-layers
' lling-llang correction-layer pipeline composition. A LayerPipeline applies its
' boxed CorrectionLayers in order — lexical → CFG → LM → custom domain layers —
' each consuming a Lattice<W,B> and returning a (typically smaller) Lattice<W,B>.
' Correction/NLP tier = amber (fill #FFF59D / border #F9A825); neutral IO = grey.
' Palette & conventions: docs/diagrams/README.md.
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam ArrowColor #607D8B
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.3
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #FFF59D
  BorderColor #F9A825
  FontColor #102027
  DiamondBackgroundColor #ECEFF1
  DiamondBorderColor #455A64
  StartColor #1565C0
  EndColor #2E7D32
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #ECEFF1
  BorderColor #455A64
}

title <b>Correction-layer pipeline</b>\n<size:11><i>LayerPipeline.apply: each CorrectionLayer maps Lattice⟨W,B⟩ → Lattice⟨W,B⟩, composed left to right</i></size>

|#ECEFF1|IO|
start
:Input lattice  Lattice⟨W, B⟩;
note right
  A weighted DAG of token
  alternatives (the WFSA the
  earlier stages produced).
end note

|#FFF59D|filtering (lexical)|
:<b>EditDistanceLayer</b> / <b>ConfusionLayer</b>\nLexical pruning & expansion —\nLevenshtein distance to a dictionary,\nconfusion-matrix substitutions;

|#FFF59D|filtering (CFG)|
:<b>CfgFilterLayer</b>\nKeep only paths a context-free\ngrammar accepts (Earley over the lattice);

|#FFF59D|rescoring (LM)|
:<b>LanguageModelLayer</b>\nReweight surviving edges by an\nn-gram / neural language model;

|#FFF59D|custom (domain)|
if (which domain layer?) then ([code])
  :<b>CodeCorrectionLayer</b>\nsyntax recovery + pattern boost;
elseif ([LaTeX]) then
  :<b>LatexSyntaxLayer</b>\ngrammar filter + validate + repair;
else ([MathML])
  :<b>MathMLSemanticLayer</b>\nhomoglyph + type checking;
endif

|#ECEFF1|IO|
:Output lattice  Lattice⟨W, B⟩\n(filtered & reweighted);
stop

@enduml
